          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1687511161942-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onions are golden, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the pot and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> (you'll use the rest later) and cook for a further 3-4 min or until caramelised – these are your <strong>balsamic onions</strong></p><p>Pat your <strong>rump steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>on both sides</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1687511168581-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1687511168581-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1687511168581-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1687511168581-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1687511168581-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>seasoned</strong> <strong>steak </strong>to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 2-3 min on each side; for medium, cook for 3-4 min on each side</p><p>Once the <strong>steak </strong>is cooked, transfer to a plate to rest</p><p>Slice the <strong>rested steak </strong>finely on a clean board</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687511179060-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1687511179060-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
